The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free.
In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored.
You'd like to your lover to think you are stylish and alluring.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please.
Your ideal relationship is comforting. You crave a relationship where you always feel warmth and love.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred.
In this moment, you think of love as commitment. Love only works when both people are totally devoted.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

this entry is all about griffin because i said so...

so anyway, griffin is a really cool cat. hes in my gym class and if he wasnt it would be so boring!! i see him in the halls like all the time and he always say, "EMILY!" and then i say, "GRIFFIN!" thats like the highlight of my day, everyday. umm, we have been friends since, i believe 4th or 5th grade...i cant quite remember. yeah, we had forts together and he likes jumping on my trampoline but hates my dog. haha. well thats about griffin! pretty awesome, right? haha ok bye

((luvs))

ok well not much to talk about so ill go through all my classes...this shall be fun!

LA(block)- ok just to put it out there, i freakin hate LA. first of all, ms.mitchell is crazy/pshyco(spelling?) and second of all, its freakin boring! we are doing a short story unit where we read all these short stories then write journal entries about them, we also have to find a theme that ties through all of them and write about that and for our final project we have to make a poster board with out partner. its easy but its soooo time consuming! 

Study Skills- i have miss. sands for study skills and i guess its ok. its not as cool as last year where you could just sit around and do nothing. this year we have to plan our whole week then she checks it, she does binder checks and every thursday we have a short lesson and assignment. and to add to it all, every friday we have to write a 2 paragraph essay about the week. actually, study skills sucks.

Gym- gym is so much worse this year. each week we increase our jogging time by a minute. by the end of the year we will be up to 10 minutes. at this moment we are running 6 minutes. o, and instead of having fitness day like once a month, we have it once a week. it sucks so much. other than that its all the same games.

Math- math is math...not much going on there. you know the usual, taking notes then doing homework, nothing exciting.

Science- we are learning about the laws of gravity or whatever. i cant really remember. but we are making roller coaster tracks in class. its really fun. i dont really like mr.mylet though. i dont think he likes me either...or kailee as a matter of fact. maybe its because he sat us right next to each other...did he think we werent going to talk? whatever, i dont care about mr.mylet.

Publications- i dont think mr.miera likes me that much either. maybe its because gabi and i talk too loud and too much. anyway, the articles i have done so far are the students of the month, CSI, America's Next Top Model and now im doing one called the stink bomb dilemma because some crazy kids have been letting off a bunch of stink bombs like in the bathrooms and in peoples lockers and just randomly in the hall. it doesnt really bug me, but i couldnt think of anything else to write...

well that was my day. exciting right? not...anyway, got to go work on homework.

((luvs))

YES! i am finally home! i went to ashland on wednesday. i hate road trip type things. i get car sick so easily and my mom wont let me sit in front and it sucks. its a 5 hour trip down there and we only stopped like once on the way down and up. i slept and listened to music all the down and up. it was pretty boring down there. i was hoping it would be sunny and semi warm but it wasnt. it was really cold. and most of the days i would just hang out in my brothers townhouse and watch CSI, even though i saw all of the episodes i watched. it was like some marathon thing for 5 days from noon to 9. and i would text message julia alot cause she was in arizona. so yeah. anyway, we walked around ashland once or twice. but its so small it only takes like 30 minutes to do it. that was pretty much my spring break. im so happy to be home! i missed my puppy! :-) anyway, tomorrows easter!

HAPPY EASTER EVERYONE!!

((Luvs))
